## Viewer role: cascade read-only to all ontology/mapping widgets

Context: The backend already rejects write calls for users whose domain
role is ``viewer`` (``PermissionMiddleware`` + ``/settings/permissions/me``
return 403 on POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE). The front-end sets
``window.isDomainViewer = true`` on viewer detection and installs a
fetch guard, but the per-widget read-only plumbing (right-click context
menus on the ontology/mapping maps, the OntoViz canvas, the shared
side-panel with its Save button, the dashboard/bridge assign buttons,
the "Add attribute"/"Remove attribute" icons, the mapping Designer &
Manual save buttons, ...) only gates on ``window.isActiveVersion ===
false``. Because version remains ``active`` for viewers, every one of
those widgets silently rendered as editable. The user could click
"Add attribute", "Assign dashboard", "Add bridge", open the right-click
menu on the canvas, type into the save-ready side panel, ... all of
which then flashed the viewer banner red when the fetch guard blocked
the eventual save — but only after confusing write intent.

This change consolidates the two read-only states: when viewer role is
detected, ``window.isActiveVersion`` is also flipped to ``false`` so
every existing ``isActiveVersion === false`` guard throughout the
codebase cascades to viewers with zero duplication. Viewers now see:
- No right-click context menu on the Ontology Map, Mapping Designer
  map, or the OntoViz designer canvas.
- No "Edit" toggle on the Business Views designer (stays view-only ⇒
  OntoViz ``viewOnly: true`` ⇒ context menu, toolbar, entity/property
  edit buttons, and add-property affordance all hidden).
- The shared side-panel opens in view mode: Save button hidden, no
  "Add attribute"/"Remove attribute" buttons, no "Assign dashboard"
  or "Add bridge" buttons, all inputs disabled.
- Mapping Designer & Manual save/auto-map/reset buttons disabled.
- Create/Rename/Delete view buttons disabled; design auto-save skipped.

Tooltip text on every disabled control is now role-aware — viewers see
"Viewer role — ask for editor/builder rights" instead of the
misleading "Load latest version to edit".

Changes:

1. src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js
   - New ``_readOnlyTooltip()`` helper returns viewer- or older-version
     wording based on ``window.isDomainViewer``.
   - ``disableEditingForInactiveVersion``, ``disableDomainMetadataViewMode``,
     ``disableDomainDocumentsViewMode``, ``disableOntologyBusinessViewsViewMode``,
     ``_disableDqCards``, ``disableMappingDesignerViewMode``,
     ``disableMappingManualViewMode``: all hardcoded
     "Read-only: Load latest version to edit" strings replaced with
     ``_readOnlyTooltip()``.
   - Navbar "Save Domain" menu-item tooltip and Documents drop-zone
     tooltip are also role-aware.
   - ``checkDomainRole``: after setting ``window.isDomainViewer = true``,
     also set ``window.isActiveVersion = false``. This is the core
     cascade: it reuses every existing read-only guard in
     ``ontology-shared-panels.js`` (``canEdit`` at lines 2098/2110 ⇒
     panel routed to ``openEntityPanelForView`` /
     ``openRelationshipPanelForView``), ``ontology-map.js`` (line 427,
     540, 566), ``ontology-design.js`` (line 81, 197, 804, 896, 968,
     1475, 607), ``mapping-design.js`` (lines 479, 568, 593, 1573,
     1827, 2292), ``mapping-manual.js`` (lines 442, 548),
     ``ontology-entities.js``, ``ontology-relationships.js``,
     ``ontology-dataquality.js``, ``ontology-swrl.js``,
     ``ontology-axioms.js``, ``ontology-assistant.js``, and
     ``domain-documents.js``. No per-module changes were needed.

