## Read-only: OWL preview no longer fails with "Unknown error"

Context: With the viewer-role cascade above (``isActiveVersion = false``
for viewers), ``autoGenerateOwl()`` in
``src/front/static/global/js/ontology-core.js`` started failing the first
time the Ontology page rendered. The function always POSTed to
``/ontology/generate-owl``, which ``Ontology.generate_owl_endpoint`` saves
into the current domain (it calls ``domain.save()``). For viewers that
POST is legitimately rejected by both the client-side
``installViewerFetchGuard`` and the backend ``PermissionMiddleware`` with
a 403 carrying ``{"error": "authorization", "message": "Viewer role does
not allow write operations"}``. The client-side handler only inspected
``result.message`` with a fallback string, which the fetch guard does not
set — so the OWL preview area showed the validation report with an
opaque "Unknown error during OWL generation" server-error block.

Fix: ``autoGenerateOwl()`` now detects read-only mode
(``window.isDomainViewer === true || window.isActiveVersion === false``)
and, in that case, issues a ``GET /ontology/export-owl`` instead. That
endpoint renders OWL from the currently loaded domain using the same
``Ontology.generate_owl`` code path, but without persisting anything, so
it passes through the permission middleware as a safe read. The
response shapes differ slightly (``{owl}`` vs ``{owl_content}``) so the
client normalises with ``result.owl || result.owl_content``. The
post-generation ``saveConfigToSession()`` call is also skipped when the
read-only endpoint is used (it was already a no-op for viewers behind
the fetch guard, but is now skipped explicitly to avoid confusing 403
logs). Error messaging additionally falls back through ``result.error``
so any future fetch-guard responses are surfaced verbatim.

Race-condition follow-up: ``window.isDomainViewer`` and
``window.isActiveVersion`` are populated asynchronously by
``version-check.js`` (``checkVersionStatus`` + ``checkDomainRole``),
while ``autoGenerateOwl`` is invoked from
``loadOntologyFromSession`` — a sibling ``DOMContentLoaded`` handler
that runs in parallel. The viewer role can therefore still look
"editable" at the moment of the first call, routing the request to
``POST /ontology/generate-owl`` and triggering a backend 403 with the
"Viewer role does not allow write operations" message the user
reported. The client now handles that explicitly: if the POST comes
back with HTTP 403, it transparently retries via the read-only GET
endpoint and flips ``usedReadOnlyEndpoint`` so the subsequent
``saveConfigToSession()`` call is suppressed. This keeps behaviour
correct under the race regardless of script ordering.

Modified files:
- src/front/static/global/js/ontology-core.js


## Read-only: belt-and-suspenders contextmenu blocker on design surfaces

Context: Even after the viewer cascade flips ``window.isActiveVersion``
to ``false``, the Mapping Designer kept showing its right-click popup
(entity, relationship, canvas variants — plus the default browser
menu). Individual D3 handlers in ``mapping-design.js``,
``ontology-map.js`` and OntoViz already gate on ``isActiveVersion ===
false``, but they share the same init-time race as
``autoGenerateOwl``: when the map is rendered before the viewer
cascade lands, some handlers cache the decision or run their
``preventDefault`` inside a conditional branch, leaving the native
menu reachable on the first interactions. Fixing every handler
individually was error-prone, so we add a single defensive blocker
that doesn't depend on per-widget state.

Fix: ``version-check.js`` now installs a document-level capture-phase
``contextmenu`` listener (``installReadOnlyContextMenuBlocker``) from
``disableEditingForInactiveVersion``. Whenever
``window.isActiveVersion === false`` and the event target is inside
any known design surface — ``#mapping-map-container``,
``#ontology-map-container``, ``.ovz-canvas``, ``.ontoviz-container``
— it calls ``preventDefault`` + ``stopPropagation`` +
``stopImmediatePropagation``, which both swallows the native browser
menu and prevents the custom D3/OntoViz menus from ever being
constructed. Capture phase guarantees we run before any downstream
handler. The installer is idempotent
(``window._readOnlyContextMenuBlockerInstalled`` latch).

This gives us a single source of truth for "no right-click in
read-only mode" that covers Mapping Designer, Ontology Map, OntoViz
Business Views canvas, and any future map container that follows the
same naming convention.

Modified files:
- src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js


## Tests: three-level permission matrix + OWL endpoint contract

Added three new test classes to ``tests/test_permission_middleware.py``
so the three domain-level tiers (viewer / editor / builder) and the
OWL-preview read-only contract are locked down:

- ``TestThreeLevelDomainRoleMatrix``: cartesian product of the three
  tiers × every HTTP method × every domain-scoped prefix
  (``/domain/``, ``/ontology/``, ``/mapping/``, ``/dtwin/``). Asserts
  viewer reads pass, viewer writes 403, editor reads + writes pass,
  builder reads + writes pass. Also checks the strict
  ``ROLE_NONE < ROLE_VIEWER < ROLE_EDITOR < ROLE_BUILDER < ROLE_ADMIN``
  ordering that the ``role_level(...) >= role_level(X)`` comparisons
  rely on.
- ``TestOwlEndpointPermissions``: locks the new read-only OWL preview
  contract — ``POST /ontology/generate-owl`` (a write) must be
  blocked for viewers and accepted for editors/builders/admins;
  ``GET /ontology/export-owl`` (the read-only fallback) must be
  reachable by all three tiers plus admin, while an app user without
  a domain team entry still gets 403.
- ``TestFilterAccessibleDomains``: covers the new
  ``PermissionService.filter_accessible_domains`` helper — admins
  (either by passed-in app_role or by live lookup) see everything
  unchanged; non-admin users only see entries where their domain
  role is not ``ROLE_NONE``; dict entries use the ``name`` key by
  default; a custom ``key=`` callback is honoured; empty input
  short-circuits without any role lookups.

Test counts: ``tests/test_permission_middleware.py`` went from 64 to
141 tests. Full suite: ``.venv/bin/python -m pytest`` — 1710 passed
in 65.50s (previously 1633).

Modified files:
- tests/test_permission_middleware.py

## Viewer / read-only: gate data-source reset and all ontology/mapping imports

User report: "in read only, data sources cannot be reset, also in
ontology and mapping no import allowed". The backend middleware
already rejects every ``POST`` on domain-scoped prefixes for viewers,
but the front-end was not hiding/disabling the triggers, so read-only
users saw clickable buttons that only surfaced a "Viewer role does not
allow write operations" toast after the round-trip.

Front-end (``src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js``):

- ``disableDomainMetadataViewMode()`` now disables the Reset button via
  its actual selector. The partial ships the reset button as
  ``<button data-meta-action="clear-metadata">`` (wired through the
  delegated ``click`` handler in ``domain-metadata.js`` at
  ``act === 'clear-metadata'``), not ``onclick="clearMetadata()"``,
  so the previous ``onclick*=`` selector was a no-op. Both selectors
  are now covered to stay robust across template refactors.
- The same routine also neutralises every other ``data-meta-action``
  write path (``open-ds-modal``, ``edit-comment``, ``table-details``,
  ``update-from-uc``, ``remove-selected-tables``, ``update-mappings``,
  ``show-load-modal``) with ``pointer-events: none`` + dimmed opacity
  + context-aware tooltip, so read-only users cannot click through
  ``<td>`` cells or dynamically rendered buttons either.
- New ``disableOntologyImportViewMode()`` disables every ontology
  import trigger: ``#importOwlLocalBtn``, ``#importOwlUCBtn``,
  ``#importRdfsLocalBtn``, ``#importRdfsUCBtn``, ``#importFiboBtn``,
  ``#importCdiscBtn``, ``#importIofBtn``, plus the FIBO/CDISC/IOF
  module checkboxes and the hidden file inputs
  (``#importOwlFileInput``, ``#importRdfsFileInput``).
- New ``disableMappingImportViewMode()`` disables the R2RML import
  buttons (``#importR2rmlLocalBtn``, ``#importR2rmlUCBtn``) and the
  hidden ``#importR2rmlFileInput`` that backs "From Local File".
- Both new routines are wired into ``disableEditingForInactiveVersion()``
  alongside the existing per-area disablers.

Back-end: no code change — the middleware already blocks viewers on
POST. The test suite is extended to pin that contract so the UI gating
and backend gating stay aligned:

- New ``TestImportAndResetEndpoints`` in
  ``tests/test_permission_middleware.py``. Parametrised across the 10
  domain-scoped write endpoints the read-only UI now disables
  (``/ontology/import-owl``, ``/ontology/import-rdfs``,
  ``/ontology/import-fibo``, ``/ontology/import-cdisc``,
  ``/ontology/import-iof``, ``/mapping/parse-r2rml``,
  ``/domain/metadata/clear``, ``/domain/metadata/save``,
  ``/domain/metadata/update``, ``/domain/metadata/update-mappings``).
  For each path: viewer → 403, editor → allowed, builder → allowed,
  admin → allowed, app user without team entry → 403.

Test counts: ``tests/test_permission_middleware.py`` went from 141 to
191 tests. Full suite: ``.venv/bin/python -m pytest`` — 1760 passed in
97.59s (previously 1710).

